U.K. Treasury Holds $229 Million of Greek Debt in Reserves

-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 
2011-07-19T12:00:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/u-k-treasury-holds-229-million-of-greek-debt-in-reserves.html
The U.K. Treasury holds 142 million
pounds ($229 million) of Greek  government bonds  as part of the
nation’s reserves, according to government accounts.  The Treasury, which published the data today in  London , is
obliged to disclose debt holdings that don’t have an investment
grade status with credit-rating companies.  The Exchange Equalization Accounts show the U.K.’s holdings
of BB rated debt account for 0.3 percent of its total. The non
investment-grade debt is due to be redeemed in full in August.
The valuation provided in today’s accounts is based on a market
rate as of March 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
 gvina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: 
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  